{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Hold a consultation & publish a national strategy for foreign language teaching",
        "additional_details": "Foreign language learning in the UK is in long-term decline, with falling GCSE and A-level uptake and a shortage of teachers.\r\n\r\nThis has consequences for the UK\u2019s global competitiveness, cultural understanding, and ability to engage internationally.\r\n\r\nWe call on the Government to publish a national strategy for foreign language education, including:\r\n\t\u2022\tmeasures to improve teacher recruitment & retention\r\n\t\u2022\tsupport for schools to expand language provision\r\n\t\u2022\tsteps to increase student participation",
        "background": "We call on Government to consult with language teachers across all educational levels & use this evidence to develop a modern national strategy for foreign language teaching.\r\n\r\nThis strategy should address curriculum content, assessment methods, & the level of difficulty in language qualifications.",
        "closed_at": null,
